AIM: to write apython program that demonstrates the use of basic data types and arithmetic operators.

ALGORITHM:
STEP 1: start the program
STEP 2: declare variables for monthly income,rent,gloceries,utilities and luxury item cost
STEP 3: calculate the total expenses by adding rent,groceriesand utilities
STEP 4: calculate monthly savings by substracting total expenses from monthly income
STEP 5: print the total expenses and monthly savings
STEP 6: calculate annual savings by mutiplying monthly saving by 12
STEP 7: calculate avg daily budget by dividing monthly income by 30
STEP 8: calculate how many luxury items can be bought using the savings
STEP 9: calculate the remaining money after buying luxury items using the modulus operator
STEP 10: display all the calculated results
STEP 11: end the program


#DATA TYPES AND ALL OPERATORS
#CODE

monthly_income = 5000
rent = 1500
groceries = 600
utilities = 300
luxury_item_cost = 450

total_expenses = rent + groceries + utilities

savings = monthly_income - total_expenses

print("Total expenses: $", total_expenses)
print("Monthly savings: $", savings)

annual_saving = savings * 12

daily_budget = monthly_income / 30

print("Predicted annual savings: $", annual_saving)
print("Average daily budget: $", daily_budget)

num_items = savings / luxury_item_cost

leftover_cash = savings % luxury_item_cost

print("You can buy luxury items:", num_items)
print("Leftover pocket money after purchase: $", leftover_cash)


